x4freetext: .NEUTRON GENERATOR OF THE INSTITUT DE PHYSIQUE
ORGANIC SCINTILLATOR SERVED AS SAMPLE AND
DETECTOR OF CARBON RECOILS AND ALPHAS.
NEUTRONS DETECTED AND THEIR TIME OF FLIGHT
MEASURED WITH RESPECT TO THESE ASSOCIATED
PARTICLES USING A SECOND SCINTILLATOR AND
ASSOCIATED CARBON RECOILS AND ALPHAS WERE
SEPARATED ON THE BASIS OF THEIR PULSE HEIGHT
AND USED TO FORM TWO NEUTRON TOF SPECTRA
SIMULTANEOUSLY BY MEANS OF A MULTIPLE FAST-
A 400 CHANNEL PHA (200 CHANNELS PER SPECTRUM).
NEUTRON DETECTOR COUPLED TO A 56AVP PHOTO-
ENERGY. DETECTOR SHIELDED FROM NEUTRON SOURCE
BY A 15 CM IRON SHADOW BAR.
NE102A SCINTILLATOR AS SCATTERER AND DETECTOR
OF ASSOCIATED PARTICLES PLACED 15 CM FROM THE
CC FOR THETA(LAB) GREATER THAN 30 DEG..
SAMPLE SCINTILLATOR USED AS REFERENCE. CROSS-
SECTION GIVEN AS 690 MB AT 14.1 MEV.
.FLIGHT PATH 169 CM (0 TO 90 DEG.) AND 130 CM
